#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(18, "And thus, the two met for the first time")[
  "You see, the only complaint I have is that we barely sing anything."

  "Well, there are just too many people, after all."

  "It seemed that Uta-nyan couldn't even comprehend such a simple fact."

  Recently, there were a couple of karaoke shops designed for smaller groups,
  which could have up to five people at most. Solo karaoke was also a thing,
  too, though a busy girl like Uta had never had such experience. It seemed like
  the "big-group karaoke session" model was slowly losing its popularity to
  those newer models.

  Uta pressed the button on the drink dispenser. Back in the karaoke room, she
  noticed that the girls on her side had finished their drinks, but they were
  too invested in watching karaoke performances to care about refilling any of
  that. She even caught glimpses of some girls picking up their cup just to put
  them down in disappointment.

  Hence, Uta decided to be a so-called "goddess", in her own words, gathering
  everyone's cups to refill their drinks. It was getting quite suffocating in
  the karaoke room, so consider that a secondary reason, too. As if mocking her
  choice of words, some girls called her a "goddess" for her actions, too.

  Since not many people were at the dispenser place, Uta could monologue her
  inner conversations without being labelled a weirdo.

  "Hmm- maybe I should go to a smaller karaoke shop with Mona and Mikoto... That
  way we can sing idol songs without having to care much about others. Idol
  song, huh? I should pick a place where we can pick songs from Internet
  sources, too."

  "Mikoto's pretty busy because of club stuff though."

  "Right. So only Mona, huh? She would probably agree if I ask her to."

  The image of Mona in Uta's mind was a timid girl who always tried her best to
  fit in with the others. Uta did find it kind of cute, and she wholeheartedly
  wanted her friend to succeed in whatever Mona was aiming for. If Uta decided
  to one day invite Mona to a two-person karaoke session, Mona would
  probably think of that as a chance to get close to Uta, and instantly accept
  Uta's invitation as a result.

  _"I mean, that time she did ditch her oshi to go to the fast food restaurant
    with me and Mikoto."_

  "Poor little Mona, getting dragged here and there by her evil friend..."

  "Wha- Please stop. Anyway, what do you think Rika would like to drink?"

  "Who knows? Aren't you her best friend?"

  "I mean she drank everything without leaving a drop of juice." Uta raised the
  cup up, trying her best to find any drop of juice remaining that could give her a
  hint.

  The flipped the cup upside down, and the only droplet of juice that could give
  her any clue fell to the floor. Uta sighed in disappointment.

  Uta had some experience with picking drinks, so she knew what exactly to
  choose in such occasions. Amongst the five types of juice in front of her, the
  "safest" choice was orange juice, possibly the most healthy due to the lack
  of carbonated gas, which was something quite a lot of people dislike. Though,
  the lack of such gas made orange juice have a pretty "plain" flavor, so she
  did not want to resort to that at all.

  After a little while of her indecisiveness, Uta finally decided on giving her
  friend some orange juice. Better safe than sorry. Which leaves only one cup
  remaining.

  "Mona, huh? This one also had nothing too."

  Knowing Mona, Uta expected her friend to be nervous from the new experience,
  so she would have to compensate by hydrating. She should be going to the
  toilet any time now.

  "She sat right next to you, so surely you had to notice what she was drinking,
  right?" Uta('s chat) said in a judgmental voice.

  "Okay, chat, please..." She instantly switched to an appeasing, yet humorous
  tone.

  "Could it be... that you don't actually know?" Uta('s chat) pressed on.

  A smirk appeared on her face, which instantly disappeared once she switched
  back to her Uta identity.

  "No, you understand right. That time at the fast food store I sat opposite to
  her so..."

  "Excuses, excuses..."

  "Look at this so-called 'friend', chat."

  Uta kept bickering with herself until she finally decided to refill
  Mona's cup with orange juice. She sighed after putting everything on the tray,
  ready for bringing the refilled cups back to everyone.

  "I swear to god, you all made this so much more harder..."

  "More like it's because of your incompetence, Uta-nyan."

  "Uta-nyan is truly an incompetent bitch who would never care about their
  friends. Even something as trivial as which drinks they like could make her
  stall five minutes for."

  "Hey! It's been three minutes at most." She turned on her phone screen, "Okay
  six minutes, I lost."

  She sighed, before picking up the tray to return to the karaoke room.

  "All right, I'm the most evil person on Earth, okay! Even that PDF file
  Hiko-nyan had nothing to compare with me, okay? I am the evil lord, the demon
  queen of human civ..."

  Uta turned her back, only to see a boy within her age staring at her with
  curious gazes.

  Admitting being someone as atrocious as a pedophile that recently got
  cancelled was definitely not something you would want to do in front of a
  stranger, but just the fact Uta was talking alone was enough to make her
  shiver from embarrassment.

  _"Wait! Did he hear all that? When did he arrive here? How did I not notice
    him? Argh- Is there a hole I could jump down right now?"_

  Once Uta calmed down a bit, she realized the boy's identity. It was
  // nagi seishiro
  Mekiru Toyama, a friend of Nagi Tadano, who was that childhood friend of Rika
  who kept arguing nonsense with her. _"He's in the karaoke group, too? I
    want to die right now."_

  On second thought, having some stranger spreading rumors about you would be
  more problematic, so this boy being someone from her group might actually be a
  good thing. She could always settle things with him later. Even so, the
  situation just improved from a bad one to a less-bad-yet-still-horrendous one,
  so for the embarrassed Uta, it was like nothing had changed at all.

  // LMFAO MOU ICHIDO LUMINOUS REFERENCE?????
  And of course, dying is not an option. Once she realized that, Uta switched
  back to her usual mode, preparing to initializing a conversation. She still
  could not hide her awkwardness, though.

  "Hey... Toyama-san, you're here to get more juice, too?"

  She tried to make a calm smile on her face, but her forced smile and her
  fingers scratching her head seemed to suggest she was not calm at the
  slightest.

  Mekiru was thrown off for a bit, before he realized that the cute girl in
  front of her was asking him a question.

  "Uhm... yes." Mekiru mumbled, directing his gaze elsewhere, "I'm refilling for
  the boys..."

  It was then when Uta realized that he was carrying a tray of empty cups just
  like her a moment ago. The timing made her suspected him of imitating her
  "goddess" act, but she was not pissed or anything. She did not have a
  copyright on the concept of "refilling juice for the group", after all.
  Though, she kind of regretted not offering refills for the boys.

  Mekiru's voice reminded Uta of her friend Mona, and by looking at his
  gestures, she could deduce that this boy was not a sociable person. In fact,
  the fact that she did not have any memory of him probably meant he tagged along
  this karaoke group in the exact same situation as Mona did. Maybe this was not
  too bad, after all, since people like him might not like to gossip about Uta's
  weirdness and was generally easier to deal with.

  Uta wanted to ask him "how much did you hear", but she was too ashamed to do
  so. The only thing she could do was make a slight bow, "I'm going first", to
  escape from the crime scene.

  _"Maybe, if God exist, I pray that he only heard the chuunibyou-esque 'evil
    lord' thing."_

  She was planning to settle this case with him in
  order to protect her reputation at school, but that could be done later.

  The moment she walked past him, her cheeks burned up with embarrassment. She
  intended to have a brief visit to the restroom to settle down, but even that
  plan of hers was ruined.

  Uta did not expect to feel a force, gently pulling on her sleeves.

  Uta glanced back, revealing her hot red cheeks to the person she did not want
  to see them the most. The boy was tugging her sleeve with two fingers, in a
  way to minimize skin contact with her.

  "About that evil thing, what exactly did you mean? Why are you comparing
  yourself with a..."

  Mekiru mumbled in a barely hearable voice, but due to the short distance, Uta
  could hear every word of it. _"Of course he heard that!"_, she thought in
  immense distress.

  "Well, I'm just joking..." Uta hesitantly replied, with a faint smile to cover
  up the storm bottling up within her mind.

  Uta had nothing else than the word "joke" to cover up her rabbit hole of
  weirdness. Even though she was someone who could regularly come up with very
  clever lines in conversations, this situation was just too tricky for her.

  "With yourself?"

  _"AHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!"_

  That was the question she did not want to hear the most.

  At that moment, Uta had thought of jumping in front of a truck, running off
  to a new world where this incident did not happen.

  _"Oh right! Rogue trucks can sometimes crash right into a building and kills
    everyone, right? Wait, no! This karaoke shop is in a small alleyway, there's
    no way a truck could crash here!"_

  What was she even thinking about at this point.

  Though, no matter how much she tried to run away from reality, the truth
  remained that she could never escape from this mess. Maybe she could die from
  shock, but the fact that she was still breathing normally show no signs of
  this happening.

  "Yeah..." Uta mumbled in a voice fainter than that of Mekiru.

  _"In the first place, how did my Uta Proximity Detector not notice him?"_

  Uta Proximity Detector, a thing that was named like a special ability from
  shounen manga, was a natural technique that Uta could harness for quite a long
  time. It was so powerful and paranormal that it might steer the whole genre
  of this novel to supernatural, but Uta really had a passive skill like that.

  This passive skill was the ability to detect human presence around the user.
  It could be used to adaptively control the volume of the user's monologuing
  according to how many people were around them. Kind of useless for normal
  people, except for someone who talked to herself all the time like Uta.

  According to her experiments in middle school, this radar system was more
  effective when tracking people with a higher status and popularity. In other
  words, it seemed to detect other presences by sensing their "aura".

  Which could mean that, Mekiru's presence was so low that her system really
  treated him as some noise, so Uta continued talking as
  if no one was there. There were a number of similar cases like this in the
  past, but the worst it got was just a "Uta-chan, did you say anything?" from
  her friend.

  _"Gosh! Even this system could detect Mona! How much of an invisible person
    you are to be able to easily bypass such a perfect system!"_

  Returning to her reality, it seemed that there were no further questions, and
  she could finally flee from everything. It would be a headache at home for her
  to think of a way to cover up everything, but until then, it seemed that she
  could still enjoy the karaoke session with her friends.

  "Well, then. I'm returning..."

  The boy nodded in silence, which finally gave Uta the chance to go back.
  The girl whose secret was leaked for the first time promptly walked away, with
  her steps gradually getting faster and faster.

  It seemed that Uta's seemingly perfect high school debut were showing cracks,
  leaking her deepest secrets to the world around her.
]
